column5: I always make a stop when I fish tri lakes, I take every single Jerry can I own with me for that ethanol free gas
That's where I go now too, only 20 minutes from home.

Most days gas is 20-25 cents a liter cheaper than in Bobcaygeon and like Lew I am about 23 kilometers away so it is worth driving there and back to save... Any time we have a reason to have to go to Buckhorn or Lakefield or Peterboro we fill up at Curve Lake even if it is only 1/4 tanks worth...
